                  <msItem  xml:id="MS_Selden_Supra_48-item1"><locus from="1r" to="444v" type="inferred"/>
                     <author key="person_79081365">Raymond of Peñafort</author>
                     <title key="work_4219">Summa de poenitentia et matrimonio</title>
                     <incipit>Quoniam ut ait Ieronimus</incipit> 
                     <note>Extensive annotation, mostly contemporary.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang></msItem>
                  <msItem  xml:id="MS_Selden_Supra_48-item1b">
                     <note><title type="desc" key="work_10409">Astronomical matter</title> is on pp. vi, 436.</note> <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang></msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Selden_Supra_48-item1a">
                     <note type="index">An alphabetical index, imperfect at the end, at p. 418
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>Financial memoranda in English are written upside down in the lower margins of pp. 218-219 ('Vnto anne houenet (?) yat I boroed of hur - ix s.', 'And I ham behynd for hur wages for a quarter - v s. at mychaellmous') and 288 ('The mone yat I layd owt at Westmaster [Westminster] ye frurst tourne - xxvj s. viij d. &amp; at ye secound tourne - xvj s. viij d. &amp; for to haue a cope of there' - xvj d.')</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="enm">Middle English</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
